schema: EXIF schema for additional EXIF properties
pdfaproperty: A name object indicating whether the document has been modified to include trapping information
UUID based identifier for specific incarnation of a document
The common identifier for all versions and renditions of a document.

A reference to the original document from which this one is derived. It is a minimal reference; missing components can be assumed to be unchanged. For example, a new version might only need to specify the instance ID and version number of the previous version, or a rendition might only need to specify the instance ID and rendition class of the original.
The creator's contact information provides all necessary information to get in contact with the creator of this news object and comprises a set of sub-properties for proper addressing.
Describes the nature, intellectual or journalistic characteristic of a news object, not specifically its content.
When true, image has a cropping rectangle.
When true, non-default camera raw settings.
File name for raw file (not a complete path).
The name of the Tone Curve described by ToneCurve. One of: Linear; Medium Contrast; Strong Contrast; Custom or a user-defined preset name
"White Balance" setting. One of: As Shot; Auto; Daylight; Cloudy; Shade; Tungsten; Fluorescent; Flash; Custom
A description of the lens used to take the photograph. For example, "70-200 mm f/2.8-4.0".
The serial number of the camera or camera body used to take the photograph.
The date and time the resource was originally created.
XMP08 Spec: An ordered array of plate names that are needed to print the document (including any in contained documents).

pdfatype: Identifies a portion of a document. This can be a position at which the document has been changed since the most recent event history (stEvt:changed). For a resource within an xmpMM:Ingredients list, the ResourceRef uses this type to identify both the portion of the containing document that refers to the resource, and the portion of the referenced resource that is referenced.
ContactInfo is a generic structure providing a basic set of information to get in contact with a person.
pdfafield: The contact information web address part. Multiple addresses can be given, separated by a comma.
The contact information phone number part. Multiple numbers can be given, separated by a comma.
The contact information part denoting the local postal code.
The contact information email address part. Multiple email addresses can be given, separated by a comma.

The contact information address part. Comprises an optional company name and all required information to locate the building or postbox to which mail should be sent. To that end, the address is a multiline field.
The contact information part denoting regional information like state or province.
